        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 6:29PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles north of Two Buttes, or 24 miles northwest of The Saunders
Elevator, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Walsh, Two Buttes, and Two Buttes Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
